sections.content:
A chapter file consists of an array called <b>stages</b>, where each stage is represented by a JSON object. The formatting is structured and readable, with each property placed on a new line. Here's an overview of the structure:<br><br><pre>{
  "stages": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Greetings, wanderer. Welcome to the realm of Erainor...",
      "properties": {
        "type": "linear",
        "next_stage_id": 2
      }
    },
    ...
  ]
}</pre><br>This structure defines the chapter's narrative flow and contains properties for each stage, such as <b>id</b>, <b>text</b>, and <b>properties</b>. The <b>properties</b> object further specifies the stage's type, next_stage_id, and other attributes. The above formatting ensures that the JSON file is easily readable and maintainable.
